    <h2>{`Summary`}</h2>
    <p>{`The DataLoader library is useful to cache data during a single request when GraphQL is traversing the tree. A parent node can look-ahead and load in batch information reducing the number of future requests. The DataLoader library cache the result for each DataLoader. In the code presented, the DataLoader was filling up the parent loader which might not be useful in the situation but by `}<em parentName="p">{`priming`}</em>{` the child's DataLoader jettisoned all costly subsequent in the child's resolver.`}</p>
